READING
Part 6   Read the message.
Dear Tom,
I know it's been a while since I last wrote, and I apologise for going quiet. Life has been rather hectic! I hope you and your family are all doing well.
The biggest change for me is that I've recently moved to a new city for work. I've been transferred to the company's regional office in Edinburgh - which is both exciting and a little daunting. I only had two weeks' notice, so the move was quite rushed. I'm renting a small flat near the city centre for now, but I'm hoping to find something larger once I've properly settled in.
Edinburgh itself is wonderful - the architecture is stunning, and there's so much history everywhere you look. I've already visited the castle twice! The locals have been very welcoming, though I have to admit the weather is quite different from what I'm used to back home. I've had to invest in some warmer clothing!
Work-wise, things are going well. My new team is talented and very supportive. I'm managing a project that involves coordinating teams across three different countries, which is challenging but also incredibly interesting. I never expected to be working at this level so soon in my career.
I'd love to visit you before the end of the year if possible. Perhaps around December, when work usually quietens down a bit. Let me know what you think!
Warm regards,
Hannah
