EVERYDAY ENGLISH
Part 8   Choose the best response to each statement. (10 points)
1. I finally passed my driving test!
a  That's terrible news.     b  About time too! Congratulations!     c  Really? How awful.
2. Would you like to come to dinner on Saturday?
a  I'd love to, thanks!     b  Yes, I've already been.     c  That's too bad.
3. My phone just completely died on me.
a  Seriously? What a pain!     b  Really? Does it often?     c  How impressive!
4. James organized the whole surprise party by himself.
a  Was he really?     b  That was so thoughtful of him!     c  Fair enough.
5. I'm completely stuck with this homework.
a  Lucky you!     b  Would you like some help?     c  Are you really?
6. Can I use the meeting room for an hour?
a  Not at all, feel free.     b  Yes please.     c  Absolutely not.
7. You've been looking tired lately.
a  Thanks very much.     b  Yes, I haven't been sleeping well.     c  Of course, no problem.
8. There's no bread left in the kitchen.
a  OK, I'll bake some later.     b  How many do you want?     c  That's quite unfair.
9. I'm pretty sure Paris is in the south of France.
a  Oh yes? What happened?     b  Actually, it's in the north.     c  Sure. What's up?
10. I've decided to start learning Japanese!
a  Not at all.     b  Wow, that'll be quite a challenge!     c  Oh yes? What happened?
____ / 10  (1 mark per answer)
